rca of the issue:
BUG: Onboarding Step 5 'Done' screen never renders.
Reproduction:
1. Register a new user via /login → toggle → submit signup. Redirects to /onboarding.
2. Fill Step 1 Company → Continue.
3. Fill Step 2 Azure Tenant (4 fields, any fake UUIDs) → Continue.
4. Fill Step 3 AI Config endpoint + key → Continue.
5. On Step 4 click [data-testid=onboarding-extract-button]. After ~10-15s the backend returns 200 with metrics.phases populated (auth/resources/cost/security=error, ai=ok with fake creds).
6. Expected: setStep(5) triggers; user sees green check, 'You\'re all set, <name>!' heading, 4 stat cards (Resources=0, VMs=0, Resource Groups=0, Security Score=0) and a Go to Dashboard button.
7. Actual: User is instantly redirected to /dashboard. Step 5 markup never paints.

Root cause: /app/frontend/src/pages/Onboarding.jsx lines 42-45
```
useEffect(() => {
  if (user === false) nav("/login", { replace: true });
  if (user && user.onboarding_complete) nav("/dashboard", { replace: true });
}, [user, nav]);
```
combined with line 108 inside finalizeExtraction:
```
await refreshUser();
```
The refreshUser() call updates AuthContext.user.onboarding_complete = true (the backend marks user.onboarding_complete=true inside /api/onboarding/submit). The above useEffect then fires with the new user object and unconditionally navigates to /dashboard, BEFORE the planned `setTimeout(() => setStep(5), 600)` on line 118 even runs (and even if it did, the navigate would still take precedence).

Mitigation (recommended): Remove `await refreshUser()` from finalizeExtraction (line 108). Instead call refreshUser() inside the StepDone 'Go to Dashboard' onClick handler right before nav('/dashboard'). The user can finish reading the success screen, then refresh + navigate when they choose. Alternative: keep refreshUser but change the redirect useEffect to ignore the moment of just-completed onboarding, e.g.:
```
const justFinished = useRef(false);
// inside finalizeExtraction success: justFinished.current = true; setStep(5);
useEffect(() => {
  if (user && user.onboarding_complete && !justFinished.current) nav('/dashboard', { replace: true });
}, [user]);
```
